The paper discusses the application of matrix factorization and autoencoder to the link prediction problem in sparse graphs, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper also proposes a new model called MF+AE, which combines both approaches. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, since the paper deals with graph datasets, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper uses dropout as a regularization technique, which is commonly used in computer vision, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
